</div>
<div id="ftn5">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref5" name="_ftn5"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[5]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">             Cf. A. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Serra</span>, <i>Memoria e contemplazione</i> (Lc 2,19.51b), dans “Theotokos” VIII (2000), p. 821-859. </span>N.B. Cette revue est une revue interdisciplinaire de mariologie, dirigée par Alberto Valentini, éditée par l’Association centro Mariano Monfortano, via Romagna, 44 – 00187 Roma.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn6">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref6" name="_ftn6"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[6]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>             2<sup>ème</sup> lecture de la veillée pascale.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn7">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref7" name="_ftn7"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[7]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>             1<sup>ère</sup> lecture du jeudi saint.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn8">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref8" name="_ftn8"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[8]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>             Cf. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Benoît</span> XVI, <i>Homélie du Jeudi Saint, 5 avril 2007</i></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn9">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref9" name="_ftn9"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[9]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>             <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">J. Bernard</span>, <i>Genèse 1-3 :</i> <i>Lecture et traditions de lectures,</i> dans Mélanges de science religieuse (1984), n°3-4, p. 109-128 ; (1986) Ibid., n°1, p. 3-55.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn10">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref10" name="_ftn10"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[10]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Vatican II</span>, <i>Lumen gentium</i> 55 et 58</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn11">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref11" name="_ftn11"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[11]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            R. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Bloch</span>, <i>Moïse homme de l’alliance,</i> Desclée 1955, p. 127-167</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn12">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref12" name="_ftn12"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[12]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Lecture d’Exode 12 le jeudi saint. Lecture d’Exode 14 durant la veillée pascale…</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn13">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref13" name="_ftn13"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[13]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II</span>, <i>À l’approche du troisième millénaire</i>, n° 48</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn14">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref14" name="_ftn14"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[14]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span>Il n’est donc pas Cyrus qui ne connaît pas Dieu et il n’est qu’un rapace (Is 45-46). Il n’est pas Sheshbaççar critiqué pour avoir entreprit la construction des murailles et n’avoir pas compris que Dieu voulait voir en Jérusalem une ville ouverte (Za 2,8), ni Zorobabel, critiqué pour avoir négligé la reconstruction du temple (Ag 1,1-4). Il n’est pas non plus Josué ayant du être purifié pour ses péchés (Za 3,1-5), ni le reste des rescapés d’Israël qui confesse ses fautes en réponse à la prédicateur du Serviteur (Is 58,1)…</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn15">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref15" name="_ftn15"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[15]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            On pourrait continuer les parallèles (Cf. Rm 15, 21 // Is 53,15 etc.) Cf. Pierre <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Grelot,</span> <i>Les poèmes du serviteur, de la lecture critique à l’herméneutique, </i>Ed. du Cerf, 29 bd Latour-Maubourg, Paris 1981, p. 145</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn16">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref16" name="_ftn16"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[16]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="NL">            Cf. Pierre GRELOT, op. cit. p. 41-43. </span><span lang="FR-BE">Mais il faudra du temps pour identifier la mère du Serviteur à la nouvelle Eve ; le serpent de Gn 3, 15 sera identifié au Diable au temps des écrits de Sagesse (Job).</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn17">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref17" name="_ftn17"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[17]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            Cf. A.<span style="text-transform: uppercase;"> Serra</span>, “<i>Bibbia”, </i>Nuovo dizionario di mariologia, a cura di de Fiores, San Paolo, Milano 1985, p.235-237</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn18">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref18" name="_ftn18"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[18]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul</span> II, SD 22</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn19">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref19" name="_ftn19"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[19]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Pie </span>IX, dans la bulle <i>Ineffabilis Deus</i> (1854), présente Marie immaculée dans la perspective de la lutte contre l’ennemi du genre humain : Marie participe à la victoire sur le démon (qui, blessé à mort peut cependant encore faire sentir son effet néfaste).</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn20">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref20" name="_ftn20"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[20]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Cf. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II</span>, <i>Salvifici doloris</i> 24.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn21">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref21" name="_ftn21"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[21]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            L’auteur spirituel qui a le mieux exploré ces chemins de transfiguration par la souffrance est sans doute saint Jean de la Croix, dans « La nuit obscure ». Mais avant lui, c’était largement déjà la théologie spirituelle du prophète Isaïe.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn22">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref22" name="_ftn22"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[22]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Cf. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II</span>, <i>Redemptoris Mater</i> 24</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn23">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref23" name="_ftn23"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[23]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            J. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Bernard</span>, <i>Torah et culte chez les Rabbins, confessions divergentes,</i> dans Mélanges de science Religieuse, Lille, Janvier-mars 1997 pp. 38-71</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn24">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref24" name="_ftn24"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[24]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II, </span><i>Redemptoris Mater</i> 19</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn25">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref25" name="_ftn25"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[25]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Même thème de « l’heure », de « la gloire », même appellation « Femme ».</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn26">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref26" name="_ftn26"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[26]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span><span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Congrégation pour le culte divin</span>, <i>Messes en l’honneur de la Vierge Marie</i>, Desclée Mame 1988, p. 207 et p. 263</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn27">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref27" name="_ftn27"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[27]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span><span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Congrégation pour le culte divin</span>, <i>Messes en l’honneur de la Vierge Marie</i>, Desclée Mame 1988</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn28">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref28" name="_ftn28"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[28]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            Cantica Rabbah 1,3.1 ed. </span><span lang="EN-GB">M. Simon, The Soncino Press, London 1977, 36</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn29">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref29" name="_ftn29"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[29]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            ibid., 37</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn30">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref30" name="_ftn30"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[30]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            Cf. A<span style="text-transform: uppercase;">. Serra</span>, <i>Memoria e contemplazione</i> (Lc 2,19.51b), dans “Theotokos” VIII (2000), p. 821-859. </span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn31">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref31" name="_ftn31"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[31]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            Ici, </span>création ex nihilo, à partir de rien.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn32">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref32" name="_ftn32"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[32]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            Ez 37, 1-14 ; Is 40, 3-5 ; Jr 31,35…</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn33">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref33" name="_ftn33"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[33]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            Cf. K.<span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Stock, <i>M</i></span><i>aria, la madre del Signore, nel Nuovo Testamento</i>, ed. ADP, Roma 1997</span></p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT">               A.<span style="text-transform: uppercase;"> Serra</span>, <i>Maria di Nazaret, una fede in cammino</i>, ed. </span><span lang="FR-BE">Paoline, Roma 1993</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn34">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref34" name="_ftn34"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[34]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            Cf. </span>R. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Laurentin, </span><i>Les Evangiles de l’Enfance du Christ</i> Desclée, Paris, 1982, pp. 434-439</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn35">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref35" name="_ftn35"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[35]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span>Les mages virent « l’enfant avec Marie sa mère » (Mt 2,11), Joseph doit fuir avec « l’enfant et sa mère » (2,13), il prend donc « l’enfant et sa mère » (2,14), et de nouveau il doit prendre « l’enfant et sa mère » (2,20), il prit donc « l’enfant et sa mère » et rentra dans la terre d’Israël (2,21).</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn36">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref36" name="_ftn36"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[36]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Saint Jean raconte aussi une union de Jésus et de sa mère (à Cana et au calvaire). Saint Mathieu et saint Jean sont donc deux traditions différentes qui convergent et se confortent mutuellement pour exprimer l’union de Jésus et de sa mère dans la perspective de la passion.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn37">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref37" name="_ftn37"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[37]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="EN-GB">            Is 49, 2 ; Sg 18, 15 ; Eph 6, 17 , Ap 1, 16</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn38">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref38" name="_ftn38"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[38]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            Cf. G.-P. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Di Nicola,</span> <i>Una maternità in discussione, </i>in “Theotokos” anno VI, 1998, n°2, p. 455-468, p. 458-461</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn39">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref39" name="_ftn39"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[39]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            En saint Marc, la foi en la résurrection est fondée sur la parole de l’homme vêtu de blanc qui redit aux femmes une parole de Jésus (Mc 16,7 : « Il vous précède en Galilée, là vous le verrez, comme il vous l’a dit »). En saint Luc, le ressuscité se fait reconnaître aux pèlerins d’Emmaüs en méditant avec eux l’Ecriture (Lc 24, 27)…</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn40">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref40" name="_ftn40"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[40]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            La formule « après trois jours » est équivalente à la formule « le troisième jour » ; elle se réfère au jour où Dieu fait grâce, comme lors du sacrifice d’Isaac, ou encore lors de l’événement du Sinaï…</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn41">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref41" name="_ftn41"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[41]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            Lc 9, 22 ; 24, 7.26.44.46</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn42">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref42" name="_ftn42"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[42]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            A. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Serra</span>, “Bibbia”, in <i>Nuovo Dizionario di Mariologia,</i> a cura di Stefano de Fiores e Salvatore Meo, ed. Paoline, Milano 1985, quarta stampa 1996, pp.240-245</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn43">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref43" name="_ftn43"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[43]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            A. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Serra</span>, op.cit.</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn44">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref44" name="_ftn44"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[44]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Les Actes des Apôtres dont l’auteur est aussi saint Luc.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn45">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref45" name="_ftn45"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[45]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span>Premier jour, le témoignage de Jean (Jn 1,19-28); le lendemain (1, 29), deuxième jour, Jean annonce Jésus l’agneau de Dieu ; le lendemain (1,35), troisième jour, André amène Simon Pierre vers Jésus; le lendemain (1,43), quatrième jour, Jésus appelle Philipe ; après cela, "le troisième jour", les noces de Cana, où Marie était là.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn46">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref46" name="_ftn46"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[46]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            M. MORGEN, <i>« La communication de la vie »,</i> dans Revue des sciences religieuses, Strasbourg, 1999, n° 4, p. 445-460</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn47">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref47" name="_ftn47"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[47]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            Mt 26,36-46 ; Mc 14, 26-42, Lc 22,39-45 </span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn48">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref48" name="_ftn48"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[48]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span>« <i>Témoigner »</i> chez saint Jean ne désigne jamais une chose extérieure, mais toujours la révélation d’un mystère caché (Jn 3,31-34 ; 1,34).</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn49">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref49" name="_ftn49"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[49]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Une théologie, qui avec Jean Paul II est une observation de la vie, une théologie existentielle, phénoménologique.</p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText">               Plusieurs fois, après une observation de l’Ecriture, nous aurons une telle approche théologique.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn50">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref50" name="_ftn50"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[50]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II</span>, Lettre apostolique <i>Salvifici Doloris (SD) </i></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn51">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref51" name="_ftn51"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[51]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span><span style="text-transform: uppercase;">J. Bernard</span>, <i>Genèse 1-3 :</i> <i>Lecture et traditions de lectures,</i> dans Mélanges de science religieuse (1984), n°3-4, p. 109-128 ; (1986) Ibid., n°1, p. 3-55.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn52">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref52" name="_ftn52"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[52]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            A. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Serra</span>, <i>Maria e la pienezza del tempo,</i> Rome 1999, p. 79-83</span></p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="IT">               A. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Serra</span>, <i>Maria a Cana e presso la Croce,</i> Rome 1991, p. 13-26 </span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn53">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref53" name="_ftn53"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[53]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II, </span>RM 19</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn54">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref54" name="_ftn54"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[54]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Cf. Henri BARUK, <i>Le judaïsme et le prophétisme hébreu devant l’idolâtrie,</i> édition Zikarone, Paris 1959</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn55">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref55" name="_ftn55"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[55]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Nous allons largement suivre Jacques <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Bernard</span>, <i>La guérison de Bethesda un jour de Sabbat,</i> Mélanges de Science Religieuse n° 1. Lille, 1977, pp 13-44.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn56">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref56" name="_ftn56"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[56]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Prière du « Shemone Esré » ou Dix huits bénédictions : « accordes-nous Notre Père, une connaissance venant de toi… » (4<sup>ème</sup> bénédiction) et « Pardonnes-nous Notre Père… » (6<sup>ème</sup> bénédiction)</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn57">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref57" name="_ftn57"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[57]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            En Gn 2,2-3 le 7<sup>ème</sup> jour est marqué d’une ambiguïté : Dieu « acheva » et « se reposa ». Les commentaires du Targum oscillent. Dans le Targum Onkelos (targum officiel du Pentateuque), Dieu se réjouit et se reposa le 7<sup>ème</sup> jour. Dans le Targum Jonathan (targum officiel des prophètes) : Dieu acheva et se reposa le 7<sup>ème</sup> jour. Dans le Targum Néofiti I : La Parole de Yahvé acheva et il y eut Shabbat et repos en sa présence le 7<sup>ème</sup> jour.</p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText">               Dans la Septante, et chez les Samaritains : Dieu acheva le 6<sup>ème</sup> jour et se reposa le 7<sup>ème</sup> jour.</p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText">               Dans le Livre des Jubilés (Inter-testament, 2<sup>ème</sup> siècle avant J-C) : ce sont des anges inférieurs qui font le travail de providence qui dure même le 7<sup>ème</sup> jour.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn58">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref58" name="_ftn58"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[58]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Dans la Mekilta de rabbi Ismaël sur Ex 31,17 : Dieu cesse le travail mais il ne cesse pas le jugement ni la miséricorde. Jugement et miséricorde sont donc des œuvres qui ne peuvent cesser ni être confiées à d’autres, pas même aux anges.</p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText">               Le traité Ta’anit 2 a.b évoque trois clés : celle des pluies, celle de la stérilité, celle de la résurrection. Elie a eu celle de la pluie (il fait pleuvoir), et celle de la résurrection (il ressuscite le fils de la veuve), mais il ne les a pas eu en même temps afin de ne pas avoir en main plus de clés que Dieu (Sanhédrin 113a).</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn59">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref59" name="_ftn59"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[59]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Cf. J. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Bernard</span>, <i>Torah et culte chez les Rabbins, confessions divergentes,</i> dans Mélanges de science Religieuse, Lille, Janvier-mars 1997 pp. 38-71</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn60">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref60" name="_ftn60"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[60]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Cf. Talmud Babylone, Traité sanhédrin</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn61">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref61" name="_ftn61"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[61]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span><span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Congrégation pour le culte divin</span>, <i>Messes en l’honneur de la Vierge Marie</i>, Desclée Mame, p. 237</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn62">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref62" name="_ftn62"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[62]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span>Jésus est la vérité. En conséquence, toute falsification de la vérité (scientifique, historique, humaine etc.) est une atteinte au Christ et à l’unité. Au contraire, oser apprendre de tout homme qui cherche la vérité, c’est faire une œuvre d’unité.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn63">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref63" name="_ftn63"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[63]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            A.<span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Serra,</span> “Segno operante di unità dei dispersi figli di Dio (Jn 11,52)”, in <i>E c’Era la Madre di Gesù (Jn 2,1). Saggi di esegesi biblico-mariana</i> (1978-1988), ed. Cens Marianum, Milano-Roma 1989, pp. 285-321. </span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn64">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref64" name="_ftn64"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[64]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="EN-GB">            Is 60,1-9 ; 49,19-20 ; Tb 13,12-13 ; Ps 87… Is 49,18-23 ; 54,1-3 ; 60,1-22 ; 66,7-13 ; Bar 4,36-37 ; 5,5-6… </span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn65">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref65" name="_ftn65"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[65]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            Les prophéties concernant Jérusalem et le temple sont accomplies en Marie et Jésus, mais cela ne refuse évidemment pas au peuple Juif le droit de revenir aujourd’hui sur la terre de ses ancêtres et d’y prier, dans le respect du droit international. </span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn66">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref66" name="_ftn66"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[66]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Saint Louis-Marie de Montfort</span><span lang="FR-BE" style="text-transform: uppercase; mso-ansi-language: FR-BE;">,</span><span lang="FR-BE"> <i>Traité de la vraie dévotion</i>, dans <i><span style="text-transform: uppercase;">œ</span>uvres complètes</i>, Seuil, Paris 1966, § 48</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn67">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref67" name="_ftn67"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[67]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II, </span><i>Dives in misericordia, </i>Lettre encyclique sur la miséricorde divine</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn68">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref68" name="_ftn68"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[68]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Cf. A la fin de cette partie, le paragraphe « La notion de coopération dans une perspective œcuménique »</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn69">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref69" name="_ftn69"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[69]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span>par exemple Ez 47, 1 ; Za 14,8</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn70">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref70" name="_ftn70"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[70]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Les symboles de l’eau et de la lumière sont justement repris dans les sacrements chrétiens du baptême et du pardon.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn71">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref71" name="_ftn71"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[71]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Cf. R.<span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Laurentin,</span> <i>Retour à Dieu avec Marie,</i> OEIL, Paris 1991, p. 87-88</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn72">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref72" name="_ftn72"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[72]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">I. de la Potterie</span>, <i>La parole de Jésus « voici ta mère » et l’accueil du disciple (Jn 19,27), </i>E<span lang="FR-BE">dizioni Marianum, Roma 1974. </span>A. <span lang="FR-BE" style="text-transform: uppercase; mso-ansi-language: FR-BE;">Serra</span>, <i>Marie à Cana et près de la croix,</i> Cerf, Paris 1983.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn73">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref73" name="_ftn73"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[73]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            C’est ce qu’on appelle la personnalité corporative.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn74">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref74" name="_ftn74"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[74]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            En des termes presque identiques, cf. Jean Paul II, R.M.45.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn75">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref75" name="_ftn75"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[75]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Jn 1,12 ; 3,11.32.33 ; 5,43 ; 12, 48 ; 13,20 ; 17,8</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn76">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref76" name="_ftn76"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[76]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            « Voici venir l’heure -- et elle est venue -- où vous serez dispersés chacun de votre côté (ta idia) et me laisserez seul. » (Jn 16,32).</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn77">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref77" name="_ftn77"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[77]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            « Le diable […] quand il profère le mensonge, il parle de son propre fond (tôn idiôn), parce qu’il est menteur et père du mensonge. » (Jn 8,44)</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn78">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref78" name="_ftn78"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[78]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            ou encore : « Quand il a fait sortir toutes celles qui sont à lui (ta idia), il marche devant elles et les brebis le suivent, parce qu’elles connaissent sa voix. » (Jn 10,4) « Il est venu chez lui, (ta idia) et les siens ne l’ont pas accueilli. » (Jn 1,11).</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn79">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref79" name="_ftn79"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[79]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            A. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Serra</span>, <i>Dimensioni mariane del mistero pasquale. Con Maria dalla Pasqua all’Assunta,</i> Paoline, Milano 1995, pp. 16-19</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn80">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref80" name="_ftn80"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[80]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT"> Cf. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">C.Maggioni,</span> <i>Benedetto il frutto del tuo grembo</i>, Portalupi 2000, p. 168-169</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn81">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref81" name="_ftn81"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[81]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a> <i><span lang="IT">L’"Ora" della Madre. Celebrazione maraiana per il sabato santo. Secondo formulario ispirato alla liturgia Bizantina,</span></i><span lang="IT"> Ed. “Mater Ecclesiae”, Roma 1983.</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn82">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref82" name="_ftn82"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[82]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Par l’expression « Mère de Dieu et du Rédempteur » (LG 53), le concile affirme que Marie est la mère de Jésus (le Verbe) en vue du salut, dans la perspective de la rédemption.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn83">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref83" name="_ftn83"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[83]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span>« La Bienheureuse Vierge Marie, Reine des Apôtres, est l’exemple parfait de cette vie semblable à celle de tous, remplie par les soins et les labeurs familiaux, Marie demeurait toujours intimement unie à son Fils et coopérait à l’œuvre du Sauveur à un titre absolument unique. » <span lang="FR-BE" style="text-transform: uppercase; mso-ansi-language: FR-BE;">Vatican II</span><span lang="FR-BE">, Décret sur l’apostolat des laïc, <i>Apostolicam </i></span><i>Actuositatem,</i> § 4</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn84">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref84" name="_ftn84"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[84]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span><span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II,</span> <span lang="FR-BE">Exhortation apostolique <i>Redemptoris Custos</i> §22</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn85">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref85" name="_ftn85"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[85]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Ainsi <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Jean Paul II</span> : « Les paroles de la prière du Christ à Gethsémani prouvent <i>la vérité de l’amour par la vérité de la souffrance. </i>Les paroles du Christ confirment en toute simplicité cette vérité humaine de la souffrance, jusqu’au fond: la souffrance, c’est subir le mal, devant lequel l’homme frémit. Il dit: « Qu’elle passe loin de moi! », précisément comme le Christ l’a dit à Gethsémani. » (SD 18)</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn86">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref86" name="_ftn86"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[86]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Cf<span style="text-transform: uppercase;">. Origene</span>, <i>Commentaire sur le Cantique des Cantiques,</i> dans SC 375, tomes I et II, par L<span style="text-transform: uppercase;">. Bresard </span>et H. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Crouzel</span>, Le Cerf, Paris 1991, <span lang="FR-BE">Livre I, 4,29 ; Tome I, p.239 ; Livre III, 5, 20 ; Tome II, p.537 ; Livre I, 4,26 ; Tome I, p.237. </span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn87">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref87" name="_ftn87"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[87]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span style="text-transform: uppercase;">            Alcuin</span>, <i>Supplément d’Alcuin</i> : PL 101, 455-456 ; <span lang="FR-BE" style="text-transform: uppercase; mso-ansi-language: FR-BE;">Humbertus de Romanis,</span><span lang="FR-BE"> <i>In Quare b.Virgini sabbatum dicatur. De vita regulari, I</i></span><i><span lang="IT">I</span></i><span lang="IT">, pp. 73-75</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn88">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref88" name="_ftn88"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[88]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span>Supplément d’Alcuin : PL 101, 455-456. <span lang="IT">Cf. Ignazio <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Calabuig</span>, <i>Il culto di Maria in occidente,</i> In Pontificio Istituto Liturgico sant’Anselmo. Scientia Liturgica, sotto la direzione di <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">A.J. Chupungco</span>, vol V, Piemme 1998. pp. 341-346</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn89">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref89" name="_ftn89"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[89]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span>Ce sont la 4<sup>ème</sup>, 5<sup>ème</sup> et 6<sup>ème</sup> raisons offertes au 13<sup>ème</sup> siècle par Humbertus de Romanis, maître général des moines prêcheurs (dominicains) : <span lang="FR-BE">In Quare b.Virgini sabbatum dicatur. </span><span lang="IT">De vita regulari, II, pp. 72-75</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn90">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref90" name="_ftn90"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[90]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            </span><span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Origène</span>, <i>Commentaire sur le Cantique des Cantiques,</i> op. cit.<span lang="FR-BE">, Livre I, 4,29 ; Tome I, p.239</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn91">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref91" name="_ftn91"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[91]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Origène</span>, op. cit<i>.,</i> Livre III, 5, 20, Tome II, p.537</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn92">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref92" name="_ftn92"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[92]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="EN-GB">            <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Origène</span>, op. cit<i>.,</i> Livre I, 4,26, Tome I, p.237</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn93">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref93" name="_ftn93"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[93]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            « Aussi bien, le Fils de l’homme lui-même n’est pas venu pour être servi, mais pour servir et donner sa vie en rançon pour une multitude. » <span lang="NL">(Mc 10,45, cf. Mt 20, 28)</span></p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><span lang="NL">               </span>« Quelqu’un a payé le prix de votre rachat » (1 Co 6,20).</p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText">               « [Toi, le Christ, l’agneau] tu es digne de prendre le livre et d’en ouvrir les sceaux, car tu fus égorgé et tu rachetas pour Dieu, au prix de ton sang, des hommes de toute race, langue, peuple et nation » (Ap 5,9)</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn94">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref94" name="_ftn94"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[94]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>                          « Grâce de Jésus… descendez dans nos âmes » : cf. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Saint Louis-Marie de Montfort,</span> <i>Méthodes pour dire le Rosaire</i>.</p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText">               Ainsi, l’agonie du Christ est un « sacrifice » qui remonte la pente pour nous donner la force d’adhérer à Dieu en surmontant nos angoisses.</p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText">               La flagellation du Christ est un sacrifice qui communique l’évidence de la vanité de tout ce qui enivre nos sens : Jésus est « Je Suis », c’est pourquoi croire en Jésus nous délivre du péché (Jn 8, 21-30), et en particulier de l’illusion de la sensualité.</p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText">               Jésus est couronné d’épines : humilié, il règne. L’orgueil de ce qui semble dominer le monde ne tiendra pas. Jésus rend témoignage à la vérité (Jn 19, 37). La vérité de Jésus règne. L’amour du Père, que Jésus révèle, règne.</p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText">               Le portement de Croix communique la grâce de tout élever vers le Père : élever nos regards, notre foi, dans une offrande, un geste d’élévation, un acte d’adhésion.</p>
<p class="MsoFootnoteText">               La crucifixion offre une grâce mystérieuse à celui qui prie devant la Croix…</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn95">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref95" name="_ftn95"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[95]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            Cf. </span>J. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Bernard,</span> <i>Le péché originel, une invention de saint Paul ?</i> Revue Ensemble n° 2, juin 1994, p. 91-106</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn96">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref96" name="_ftn96"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[96]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            Jn 18, 1-12 et Jn 19, 38-41</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn97">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref97" name="_ftn97"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[97]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>            C’est pourquoi nous parlons de l’Immaculée conception dans la partie sur la Passion.</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn98">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref98" name="_ftn98"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[98]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="FR-BE">            Encyclique <i>Ad diem illum laetissimum</i> (1904)</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn99">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref99" name="_ftn99"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[99]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">            Françoise B<span style="text-transform: uppercase;">reynaert</span>, <i>Cronaca del XIV simposio internazionale di mariologia, Pontificia facoltà teologica Marianum,</i> Roma 7-10 ottobre 2003, In Miles Immaculatae, Anno XXXIX fasc II, 2003, pp. 560-577</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn100">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref100" name="_ftn100"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[100]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>          <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Saint Louis-Marie de Montfort,</span> <i>Traité de la vraie dévotion, Œuvre complètes, </i>Seuil, Paris 1966, § 219-221</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn101">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref101" name="_ftn101"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[101]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>          « En outre, dans le dialogue oecuménique, les théologiens catholiques, fidèles à la doctrine de l’Eglise, en conduisant en union avec les frères séparés leurs recherches sur les divins mystères, doivent procéder avec amour de la vérité, charité et humilité. En exposant la doctrine, ils se rappelleront qu’il y a un ordre ou une "hiérarchie" des vérités de la doctrine catholique, en raison de leur rapport différent avec les fondements de la foi chrétienne. » <span lang="EN-GB">(<span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Vatican II</span> , <i>Unitatis Redintegratio </i>11) </span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn102">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref102" name="_ftn102"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[102]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="EN-GB">          Saint Bernard, saint Thomas d’Aquin…</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn103">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref103" name="_ftn103"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[103]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a><span lang="IT">          Cf. F. BREYNAERT <i>Cronaca del XIV simposio internazionale di mariologia, Pontificia facoltà teologica Marianum, Roma 7-10 ottobre 2003,</i> In “Miles Immaculatae”, Anno XXXIX fasc II, 2003, pp. 560-577, p. 568</span></p>
</div>
<div id="ftn104">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref104" name="_ftn104"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[104]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>          <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Eglise catholique, Fédération luthérienne mondiale,</span> <i>La doctrine de la justification, déclaration commune,</i> Le Cerf, Paris1999, n° 27</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn105">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref105" name="_ftn105"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[105]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>          Le groupe des Dombes a publié en 1997 <i>Marie dans le dessein de Dieu et la communion des saints. Tome I Dans l’histoire et l’Ecriture </i>; et en 1998, <i>Marie dans le dessein de Dieu et la communion des saints, tome II Controverse et conversion.</i> Le thème évoqué est abordé au tome II, n°219-222</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn106">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref106" name="_ftn106"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[106]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>          A. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Birmelé</span>, <i>Le salut en Jésus Christ dans les dialogues œcuméniques,</i> Le Cerf, Paris 1985, p.68</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn107">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref107" name="_ftn107"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[107]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>          cf. J. <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Bernard</span>, <i>Torah et culte chez les Rabbins, confessions divergentes,</i> dans Mélanges de science Religieuse, Lille, Janvier-mars 1997 pp. 38-71</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn108">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref108" name="_ftn108"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[108]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>          <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Eglise catholique, Fédération luthérienne mondiale,</span>, op. cit. n° 21, p. 68</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn109">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref109" name="_ftn109"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[109]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>          <i>Catéchisme de l’Eglise catholique,</i> Plon, Paris 1992, n°488</p>
</div>
<div id="ftn110">
<p class="MsoFootnoteText"><a title="" href="#_ftnref110" name="_ftn110"><!-- [if !supportFootnotes]--><span class="Caractredenotedebasdepage"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: FR; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">[110]</span></span><!--[endif]--></a>          Martin <span style="text-transform: uppercase;">Luther,</span> <i>Le Magnificat, Commentaire.</i> <span lang="EN-GB">Edition Salvator, Mulhouse 1967<i>, </i>p. 60</span></p>
